parameters:
"Wow... it's beautiful... I never knew such a place existed.
It's my first time here..."

"It's quite far from our town, so it's no surprise you
didn't know about it."

"...I'm sorry, Makoto. Because I was a coward, I ended up
hurting you that day."

"What's gotten into you all of a sudden, Mamoru? And what do
you mean coward? Aren't you the brave man who didn't
hesitate to save me?"

"No, that's not true. If I had just a little more courage, I
could have said it properly back then."

"But today... today I will say it. Makoto, there was
something I really wanted to tell you back in the infirmary
that day."
"Something you wanted to say... could it possibly be...?"

(Alright, I'll say it... I have to say it... I'll tell
Makoto that I like her...)

"So-Sorry Mamoru... I suddenly got a call... can you wait
just a moment?"

"What is it... I told you I was busy today... now, right
now? But, I can't right now..."

"...Understood. I'll be there right away... No, don't pick
me up. I'll catch a taxi."

"Are you done with the phone? Then, I'd like you to hear the
rest of what I was saying..."

"...I'm sorry Mamoru, something urgent came up. I have to go
back to town right now."

"Wh-What... wait, Makoto! At least... at least let me finish
what I was saying!"

"...Mamoru. About that continuation, could you let me hear
it tomorrow instead?"

"Tomorrow? I don't mind, but... didn't you have plans
tomorrow?"

"...It's okay. I'll end things with that person today. After
that, I want to meet you here again."

(That person...? Relationship...? Could it be that Makoto is
being troubled by Suzuki...!)

"Mamoru... let's meet here again tomorrow at this time...
see you...!"

"Ah! Wait, Makoto! What the... she's out of sight in no
time."

"Even if I chase after her now, I might not make it... No
choice. I'll have to check all the places Makoto has been
to."

"I've saved Makoto many times before. This time should work
out too...! I need to find Makoto quickly!"

How many hours did I spend searching for Makoto? I checked
every place I could think of, including the downtown area
and the neighboring town, but I couldn't find a single clue
about her whereabouts.

Eventually, I started receiving calls from my parents on my
smartphone, and reluctantly, I decided to head home. I tried
calling Makoto several times after that, but I never got
through.

The next day. I was back at the park with a bouquet in hand.
I hadn't managed to find Makoto, but I at least wanted to
keep our promise.

But no matter how long I waited, Makoto didn't show up. The
sky turned red, the sun set, and it became completely night,
making it difficult to wait any longer, so I reluctantly
went back home.

(I couldn't meet Makoto, and I got scolded by my parents...
it's been a terrible day... but she didn't come no matter
how long I waited, maybe something did happen.)

(At this point, I might as well go see Suzuki directly.
Maybe then I'll be able to find some clue...)

(Hm? It looks like I've got an email on my computer. Who
could it be from... eh?)

"Wow... it's beautiful... I never knew such a place
existed..."

"It's quite far from our town, so it's no surprise you
didn't know about it."

"...I'm sorry, Makoto. Because I was a coward, I ended up
hurting you that day."

"What's gotten into you all of a sudden, Mamoru? And what do
you mean coward? Aren't you the brave man who didn't
hesitate to save me?"

"No, that's not true. If I had just a little more courage, I
could have said it properly back then."

"But today... today I will say it. Makoto, there was
something I really wanted to say to you back in the
infirmary that day."
"Something you wanted to say... could it be...?"

(Alright, I'll say it... I have to tell her... that I like
her...)

"So-Sorry, Mamoru... I suddenly got a call... Can you wait
just a moment?"

"What do you want... I told you I was busy today...
What...!? Don't tell me you're... watching from somewhere
even now..."

"...You want me to come right now? Don't joke with me!! I'm
in the middle of an important conversation with Mamoru!!"

"Once this is over, I'll give you all the time you want!! So
don't call me again!!"

"Ma-Makoto...? Did something happen...? You were shouting so
loudly..."

"...It's nothing, Mamoru. More importantly, let's continue
what we were talking about."

"Eh? Oh, yeah... So, once again... I've always liked
you...!"

"Wh-What do you want!? Is there something you need from
us...?"

(Wait a minute. Isn't that sunglasses guy one of Suzuki's
henchmen? Could it be that he's here on Suzuki's orders...?)

"...You've gotten too cocky, Asahi Makoto. The young master
is furious. You'd better be prepared."
"What about the monk next to her? Are we taking him too?"

"Yeah, the orders are to bring him along. If he resists...
losing an arm won't be a big deal."

"Damn... they came so quickly...! Mamoru! Run away
quickly...!"

"The two of them have been taken away by dangerous men,
haven't they?"

"Yes. Makoto-sama mentioned they were Suzuki's
subordinates."

"We happened to see Makoto-sama and followed her... We never
expected it to turn out like this..."

"We were planning to eliminate that glasses-wearing man
after the confession... but it seems we must change our
plans now..."

"We absolutely cannot forgive anyone who hurts Makoto-sama!
Are both of you ready?"

"Yes, I've already contacted our people at home. Let's show
those men what hell looks like."
